items.name: Mirai Kasuga/春日未来 | MILLION LIVE!/ミリオンライブ/ミリシタ
items.description:
LoRA model of Mirai Kasuga (春日未来) from media-mix project THE IDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! (アイドルマスターミリオンライブ！).

The trigger word is mirai kasuga (million live). It's well known that hairclip is Mirai-chan's most notable feature, but I notice that many official illustrations don't contain it, perhaps meaning that the hairclip may be optional. When using this model, you may need add hairclip (or a specific type of hairclip e.g. pink hairclip/x hairclip/star hairclip) tag into your prompt if you want its appearance in your illustration. Besides, you can use tags such as hair scrunchie/hair bow/hair ornament/hair flower to adjust the item for holding Mirai-chan's side ponytail in place.

The LoRA weight of samples is 0.85; you can also try other weights. The greater the weight, the closer the character style is to the game card of THE IDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! THEATER DAYS (ミリシタ) and the new tachie drawn after the release of the game.

Note: I load my LoRA model through the additional network WebUI plugin, so the prompt of sample illustrations don't contain <lora:XXX:X> tag.

I'll appreciate it if you're willing to use this LoRA model and share AI arts to other people. My models and illustrations are free for everyone, and if you like them, please support me at Patreon or 爱发电.

————————————

跨媒体企划《偶像大师 百万现场》的角色春日未来的LoRA模型

示例图的LoRA权重为0.85，您也可以尝试其他权重值。权重越大，角色风格越接近游戏《偶像大师 百万现场 剧场时光》（MLTD）游戏卡面以及该游戏发行后新绘制的立绘

items.name: Gravity Falls - Giffany
items.description:
If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) for the sake of motivation and stuff ;D

For usage guidance, look into the About this version box for more information and click on Show more to get all trigger words and combinations (The trigger words in the Details box are a pain to manage).

Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

About

Let's be honest, this "accidental artificial intelligence" is the perfect mascot for anything AI related. And surely there are worst ways to unalive yourself by getting uploaded into a computer by a yandere ai that loves you... But I am still not sure if its pronounced Jiffany or Giffany which could be problematic in the long run of an relationship...

Training

This one was ... exhausting... There is only one episode of Gravity Falls where she appears so quite literally every frame counts! In v1 the Cable Bow was not correctly detected at all and its still not perfect but 25% success is still better than 0% ^^ Maybe there will be a v2 when I am bored and try some training trickery... I have some ideas but my training queue is packed ;D

items.description:
This LoRA is based on screen captures from Magical Girl Lyrical Nanoha StrikerS and is trained on keyframes of Lutecia Alpine, a.k.a. Lulu. The strength of the LoRA should be anywhere between 0.6 and 0.8. The recommended tags are: lutecia alpine, 1girl, expressionless.

Note that her design has many intrinsic details on her arms, clothes, and forehead. Getting those details in a LoRA turned out to be exceedingly hard for me. I believe that I have her art style and general appearance down, but those details make this model a bit harder to get pleasing results from.

Trained 29 images on (Тренировал 29 изображений на) -

ReV Animated https://civitai.com/models/7371/rev-animated

Used this VAE (Использовал этот VAE ) - kl-f8-anime2.ckpt

Negatives (Негативы):

https://civitai.com/models/16993/badhandv4-animeillustdiffusion

https://civitai.com/models/5224/bad-artist-negative-embedding

https://civitai.com/models/17083?modelVersionId=20170

https://civitai.com/models/7808/easynegative

The only drawback of this LORA (Единственный недостаток этой LORA):

LORA on artstyle with dark and blue colors produces a bright yellow vignette around the image. I tried for a long time to fix it manually with photoshop, but with my skills it only gets worse in the end. Alas, the original images in the frames (which I also upscaled) were with just such an effect around, cropping it would be equal to cropping a verified frame in the composition, and it’s difficult for me to cover it up (if there are those who want to help fix this problem, you can write in the comments and I will try to send a dataset so that after the correction, train LORA again with the same settings)

LORA на артстайл при темных и голубых цветах выдает яркую желтую виньетку вокруг изображения. Я долго пытался пофиксить это при помощи фотошопа вручную, но с моими навыками по итогу все выходит только хуже. Увы оригинальные изображения в рамках (которые я еще и апскейлил) были именно с таким эффектом вокруг, обрезать его равнялось бы обрезанию выверенного кадра в композиции, а замазывать это для меня трудновато (если есть желающие помочь в исправлении данной проблемы - можете написать в комментах и я попытаюсь прислать датасет чтобы после исправления снова тренировать LORA с теми же настройками)

CONCEPT EXPLANATION (ОБЪЯСНЕНИЕ КОНЦЕПТА):

I am a fan of the game series "The Witcher" and a little fan of the book series (I went through all the parts, listened to all the books and was satisfied and I recommend the same to you). So in the 1st part of the game there were almost no bed scenes, unlike the cool cg scenes from the 2nd and 3rd parts. Instead, they gave you a collection card (right now, developers are executed for this). Moreover, in the 1st part, the Witcher managed to get laid with probably every peasant woman, princess, sorceress, dryad and even ghoul, which cannot be said about the subsequent parts where his love affairs decreased)).

Я фанат игровой серии "Ведьмак" и немного фанат книжной (прошел все части, прослушал все книги и остался доволен и вам того же рекомендую). Так вот в 1ой части игры постельных сцен почти не было в отличии от навороченных сцен из 2ой и 3ей части. Вместо этого тебе давали коллекционную карточку (щас разработчиков за такое казнят). items.name: Scanno Glitch
items.description:
Overview:

Trained on 70 hand-scanned/glitched images, this LoRA produces imagery with a variety of scanographic glitch effects ranging from moderately subtle to lush lofi chaos. Originally intended for use with more photorealistic models but also plays well with Anime and Illustration focused Checkpoints and LoRAs. A great resource for those who need quick glitched assets to collage or throw some type over.

Recommended Settings:

  • LoRA Weight: 0.6+ | 0.7-0.8 sweet spot | 1 - 1.2 feeling spicy.

  • Models: v1-5-pruned-emaonly (trained on), ProtoGen_X3.4-pruned-fp16, realisticVisionV20_20, f222

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

  • Clip skip: 1 or 2

  • Resolution: All standard resolutions up to 512 x 1024 seem fine, 1024 x 1024 is where quality seems to fall off.

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 25-50

  • CFG: 7

Example Prompt:

Model: v1-5-pruned-emaonly

Steps: 30, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 3948837425, Size: 640x640

Posetive: (detailed:1.1), portrait photography in the style of <lora:scanno_Glitch_01:0.8>, (mall:1.1), golden hour, cinestill, portra, nasa backrooms, 90s, nostalgic, play area, indoors

Negative: n/a

A note on image quality:

The learned style relative to the training set is very accurate. Everything from how the images look printed on matte lightweight paper stock, to the small size of each image per page affecting the scanned output, the results are images that can appear to be lower resolution than they actually are (especially at full strength). In future versions I'll try to remedy this by scanning larger images individually, rather than many per sheet. In the meantime, however, this LoRA is a lean, mean, vibey lofi machine ;).

The IWI X95 (formerly known as the Micro-Tavor, MTAR, or MTAR-21) is an Israeli bullpup assault rifle designed and produced by Israel Weapon Industries (IWI). It is part of the Tavor rifle family, along with the TAR-21 and the Tavor 7.

The Tavor X95 can be easily distinguished from the TAR-21 (as well as from CTAR-21, STAR-21, and GTAR-21) by the location of the charging handle. The X95's charging handle is closer to the pistol grip, whilst the TAR-21's charging handle is closer to its muzzle. The X95 also features a redesigned buttstock and a magazine release near the pistol grip.

With the use of a relatively simple conversion kit, the Tavor X95 can be converted from a 5.56mm assault rifle to a 9mm submachine gun. A suppressor can also be added to the weapon, either as part of the 9mm conversion kit or as part of a replacement hand guard which integrates the muzzle brake, suppressor, and hand guard. The Tavor X95 also has its own underslung grenade launcher, the X95 GL40. A discontinued production model of the X95, the X95-GL, had the capability to mount a M203 grenade launcher on an extended notched barrel.

When configured to fire 9mm rounds, the gun uses simple blowback operation to cycle, whilst using the same body as the gas-operated rifle system. When in the submachine gun configuration, it is fed from Colt 9mm SMG magazines. A suppressor can be mounted that allows for the use of standard velocity 9mm ammunition, not specialized subsonic ammo. The barrel is the same length as the rifle version, but has a 1:10 in rifling twist to stabilize heavy 9mm bullets.

Compared to the 890 mm (35 in) long M4 carbine (with its stock extended) with a 370 mm (14.6 in) barrel, the X95 is 580 mm (22.8 in), 640 mm (25.2 in), or 670 mm (26.4 in) long, with either a 330 mm (13 in.), 380 mm (15.0 in), or a 419 mm (16.5 in) barrel, respectively.

In November 2009, the Tavor X95 was selected as the future standard issued weapon of the Israeli infantry.

This lora is a likeness of Melissa Joan Hart.

From: Clarissa explains it all (no training images from this, too young), sabrina the teenage witch, gods not dead 2.

So a few things for her at this point. Do not use at full strength, I need to cut the training down a bit. Try 0.6 or 0.7 . Also this is the most sensitive to the chosen sampler. If you get pixelization, try a different one. I used Realistic Vision for my checkpoint.

Finally please remember this is not reddit. I accept constructive feedback, but if you are toxic it lessens my desire to improve the model and make new ones.

items.name: Scrap Shitizen | Spaceships
items.description:
Scrap Shitizen

This is my first attempt at making a LoRA from the spaceships of the game you all know and love.

What does it know?

  • Ships Manufacturers

  • Ships Models

  • Views (front,side,rear,top,bottom,isometric, etc.)

What does it not know

  • Specific parts, i.e. Landing gear, guns, turrets etc.

  • Interiors, including cockpits

  • When the BMM will be released.

Notes

This is LoRA feels a bit wild but I could just be bad at prompting (very likely), keep the weights lower if it goes too crazy.
